      "rationale": "Validation experiments used FDA generic pump geometry at CPB-relevant flow rates (2–6 L/min) and speeds (2500–3500 RPM). Blood analog fluid matches clinical viscosity range. Reynolds number regime (Re 3,200–9,800) consistent with clinical CPB. Validation relevance score assessed as Adequate per ASME V&V 40 Table 3."
